snippet.textDisplay:
I've been waiting for this to come up on your channel since I first tried this recipe from your cookbook. It's become a staple in my household. My boyfriend's brother is the pickiest eater in the world and went his whole life hating beans. We peer pressured him to have some one time, and it's changed his life. He wouldn't even look at a legume before, and now he's constantly asking if we want to make this for dinner. We had a container with 20lbs of rice in our cabinet that hadn't been used in months, but we recently had to buy more just because of this dish.


I, myself, have never liked onions in any form, but for whatever reason opted to keep them in the first time we threw this together. Now I like onions, and I'm kind of mad about it. I went 23 years hating onions, YSAC. TWENTY-THREE Y E A R S. Do you know what it's like to spend that long hating a certain kind of food, just to have someone come along and make it make sense as an ingredient? Like, I finally understand why people like onions so goddamn much. I owe onions an apology. It was never the onions' fault, it was mine for being so distastefully closed-minded and not giving them the proper respect they deserve. This comment is getting long and it's about time for my nightly sacrifice to Allium cepa for my transgressions, so I'm gonna end it here.


10/10 video, as always.

snippet.textDisplay: To rinse your rice you just need a bowl and water, and of course some rice, but hey I'm not your boss. Put rice in bowl, whirl it with your hands. Massage it seductively. If the water turns white, you have successfully rinsend, and seduced your rice. Slowly tip the bowl to an angle, as to let out the white love water, but be careful and make sure the rice stays at the bottom of the bowl. Once you can see the rice stop. Rinse and repeat until the water stays clear and then, same as before, let out the water, this time entirely, but hold your hand at the corner of the bowl, as to catch any rice that might flow out. Continue with the rest of the video.
